151
00:08:40,277 --> 00:08:41,597
to do it.

152
00:08:41,957 --> 00:08:42,717
I've

153
00:08:43,757 --> 00:08:45,318
got it ready for you.

154
00:08:51,077 --> 00:08:51,757
Your Highness,

155
00:08:52,318 --> 00:08:53,438
I've talked to the physician.

156
00:08:53,438 --> 00:08:55,000
They're preparing
medicine for Young Master Jian.

157
00:08:57,717 --> 00:08:58,318
Leave now.

158
00:09:00,197 --> 00:09:01,637
Aren't you the heir's guard?

159
00:09:03,438 --> 00:09:04,038
Your Highness.

160
00:09:04,637 --> 00:09:06,757
I have to risk my life to report something.

161
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:09,238
Go ahead.

162
00:09:11,857 --> 00:09:12,800
Would my father believe it?

163
00:09:14,957 --> 00:09:16,277
He's in a high position.

164
00:09:16,478 --> 00:09:17,800
Of course he's afraid of assassination,

165
00:09:18,478 --> 00:09:20,038
especially by the heir
that he has appointed

166
00:09:20,038 --> 00:09:21,118
for over 30 years.

167
00:09:22,238 --> 00:09:23,717
The heir has reserved sufficient power.

168
00:09:24,438 --> 00:09:25,717
The prince would believe it

169
00:09:26,597 --> 00:09:27,438
even if he's reluctant.

170
00:09:30,038 --> 00:09:30,837
Don't follow me.

171
00:09:31,478 --> 00:09:32,837
I want to walk alone.

172
00:09:45,517 --> 00:09:47,157
I served beside the heir just now.

173
00:09:47,478 --> 00:09:48,118
He said

174
00:09:48,837 --> 00:09:51,177
you must be bearing a grudge
against him because of Young Master Jian.

175
00:09:51,798 --> 00:09:53,478
Rather than of being deposed by you,

176
00:09:53,918 --> 00:09:54,680
it would be better...

177
00:09:54,998 --> 00:09:55,720
It would be better...

178
00:09:56,318 --> 00:09:56,998
What is it?

179
00:09:57,478 --> 00:09:58,397
He'd rather strike first.

180
00:10:07,517 --> 00:10:08,197
Make way.

181
00:10:08,397 --> 00:10:10,038
Why should I?

182
00:10:10,517 --> 00:10:12,397
Don't you see I'm working?

183
00:10:13,077 --> 00:10:14,837
Take a detour.

184
00:10:16,597 --> 00:10:17,438
Why don't you...

185
00:10:17,517 --> 00:10:18,038
Mao Da.

186
00:10:22,798 --> 00:10:24,678
Greetings, Your Highness.

187
00:10:29,277 --> 00:10:30,397
I guessed

188
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:32,157
you could hold out.

189
00:10:32,837 --> 00:10:34,637
Surprisingly, you're living well.

190
00:10:35,957 --> 00:10:37,118
You're contented

191
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:38,878
with peace of mind.

192
00:10:39,438 --> 00:10:39,918
Very well.

193
00:10:40,918 --> 00:10:42,318
Not really.

194
00:10:42,918 --> 00:10:44,277
I'm only able to endure loneliness.

195
00:10:44,717 --> 00:10:46,077
It's not difficult to endure loneliness.

196
00:10:48,517 --> 00:10:49,438
It's difficult

197
00:10:50,878 --> 00:10:51,998
to endure injustice.

198
00:10:52,397 --> 00:10:53,358
With your words,

199
00:10:55,438 --> 00:10:57,118
I could endure any injustice

200
00:10:57,597 --> 00:10:58,478
in the world.

201
00:10:59,118 --> 00:11:00,238
I believe in you

202
00:11:01,358 --> 00:11:02,358
but I can't save you.

203
00:11:02,717 --> 00:11:03,517
Do you hate me?

204
00:11:04,757 --> 00:11:06,478
You're the master of Quliang,

205
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:08,438
but there're still things you can't do.

206
00:11:09,878 --> 00:11:11,040
No matter how great your power is,

207
00:11:11,918 --> 00:11:13,238
they're your family after all.

208
00:11:18,517 --> 00:11:19,318
Family?

209
00:11:22,318 --> 00:11:23,438
Can't Quliang

210
00:11:25,318 --> 00:11:26,998
tolerate my family?

211
00:11:35,238 --> 00:11:36,157
The weather is getting cold.

212
00:11:36,878 --> 00:11:38,440
This place is colder
than the southern outskirts.

213
00:11:39,397 --> 00:11:40,597
I'll let Yu Dechang

214
00:11:40,597 --> 00:11:41,678
send you some tailors

215
00:11:42,238 --> 00:11:42,757
and...

216
00:11:50,118 --> 00:11:50,558
No.

217
00:11:51,157 --> 00:11:54,678
Maybe you could leave the courtyard soon.

218
00:11:55,837 --> 00:11:56,920
I hope your words will come true.

219
00:11:58,238 --> 00:12:00,118
I'm leaving. Go back.

220
00:12:01,918 --> 00:12:03,318
Have a safe trip, Your Highness.

221
00:12:14,238 --> 00:12:15,277
Luckily,

222
00:12:15,397 --> 00:12:16,558
today,

223
00:12:16,757 --> 00:12:18,517
you stopped me, Ms. Lian.

224
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:19,717
Otherwise,

225
00:12:19,957 --> 00:12:21,717
I would've ended up scolding the prince.

226
00:12:27,358 --> 00:12:28,678
Forget about staying in the courtyard.

227
00:12:30,318 --> 00:12:31,038
(Look, Your Highness.)

228
00:12:31,617 --> 00:12:32,640
The bird has fallen to death.

229
00:12:33,277 --> 00:12:34,197
The birds

230
00:12:34,878 --> 00:12:36,238
